
1. How to use the testcase 'csky-dmatest' ?

1) build the testcase when building the linux kernel

	The case 'csky-dmatest' can only be used in kernel.

	build steps:
	a) Copy csky-dmatest.c into drivers/dma/
	b) Add the following line into drivers/dma/Makefile:
		obj-y += csky-dmatest.o
	c) Rebuild the kernel.

2) run the testcase

	a) The case will automatically run when booting the kernel.

	b) In the shell, you can run the case by:
		echo 1 > /sys/module/csky_dmatest/parameters/run

